<BaseLayout title="Hearthcrest Caller" description="A large backward-walking elder herbivore of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">World · Animals</p>
    <h1>Hearthcrest Caller</h1>
    <p class="lede">A large dinosaur-like elder herbivore with a warm crest, mouth-light signalling, low humming vibration, and a symbiotic feeding cycle with Amethyst Orblights.</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-artefacts">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>◎</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Elder fauna</p>
        <h2>Huge, careful, and not a monster</h2>
        <p>The Hearthcrest Caller is one of Vaelinya’s dinosaur-type elder fauna. It belongs to large-animal care, warm feeding grounds, and Rimaeri balance ecology.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h2>How to recognise it</h2>
      <p>A Hearthcrest Caller has a large herbivore body, strong hindquarters, broad feet, a deep chest, a long neck, a prominent warm crest, and a mouth-light.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h2>How it moves</h2>
      <p>The Hearthcrest Caller avoids wind in its face, turns partly away from the wind, tilts its head sideways to see where it is going, and walks backwards as normal travel.</p>
      <p>As it moves, it makes a low repeated warning call so smaller creatures can move clear.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Why it walks backwards</h2>
      <p>Its crest, mouth-light, scent membranes, and heat organs are sensitive to direct wind. Wind can disturb mouth-light grammar, crest hum, feeding-window signals, Amethyst Orblight gathering, and scent or air-pressure reading.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h2>What it does in the world</h2>
      <p>The Hearthcrest Caller supports Amethyst Orblight breeding cycles, warm dung nurseries, Crestwarm Beetles, grassland renewal, heat exchange, and large animal route memory.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h2>Relationship with Amethyst Orblights</h2>
      <p>Amethyst Orblights gather near the Hearthcrest Caller during feeding windows. Their violet glow and low hum are part of a larger symbiotic cycle involving warmth, feeding, eggs, larvae, and dung nurseries.</p>
      <div class="link-list">
        <a href="/world/animals/amethyst-orblight/">Amethyst Orblight</a>
        <a href="/world/animals/">Animals of Vaelinya</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility note</p>
      <p>The Hearthcrest Caller is a large crested herbivore that walks backwards to protect its wind-sensitive face and makes a low repeated warning sound so smaller creatures can move clear.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
